Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.15,0:09:30.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look at the wine glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:30.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look at the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:30.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look at the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.72,0:09:30.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,Look at the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.66,0:00:04.93,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Shines with a flash, and pierces with a shatter, you can't stop it once it begins to move!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.33,0:00:07.05,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Today's case is a treasure hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:09.11,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A small hint turns out to be big.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.11,0:00:10.76,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeing the one and only truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.76,0:00:12.60,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I look like a child but have mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.60,0:00:14.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My name is Meitantei Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.39,0:01:39.17,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}After helping a toy manufacturing company,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.17,0:01:44.20,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Professor Agasa received a sum of money, and took Genta and the others on a treasure hunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.77,0:01:49.40,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We arrived at the villa where the Professor's uncle lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.92,0:01:52.96,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}However, it's been fifty years since Agasa's Uncle died,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.28,0:02:00.55,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}but we've found some things to suggest that someone had been living inside the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.95,0:02:05.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Underneath objects such as vases and plates,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.69,0:02:09.89,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}we found engraved symbols of the sun, moon, and the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.69,0:02:14.67,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The toys hidden by the professor for the treasure hunt were discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.67,0:02:17.73,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}completely destroyed, most likely by that same someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.37,0:02:22.04,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There's a big secret hidden within this villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.37,0:02:29.81,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As we searched the villa, we discovered nine things engraved with the secret code:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.51,0:02:32.21,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a card,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.88,0:02:34.25,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a French dictionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.25,0:02:35.28,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a record,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.62,0:02:37.42,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}an airplane,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.29,0:02:39.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a wine glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.69,0:02:40.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}a portrait,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.77,0:02:42.79,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and lastly, a mechanical doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.19,0:02:52.43,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Also, Professor Agasa remembered seeing the same Symbols, on letters that he received from his aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.94,0:02:58.84,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The interesting thing is, the Professor showed those letters to a mystery novelist, my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.38,0:03:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he understood it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the code is written in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.93,0:03:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiragana!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.56,0:03:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.24,0:03:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hiragana?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:11.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it looks like the one who sent those letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.40,0:03:19.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one who wrote the secret code, are indeed the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.90,0:03:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, why did that man write to my aunt in a secret code?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.13,0:03:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides your aunt, is there anyone else who had access to those cards?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.01,0:03:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, my aunt mentioned that Someone weird was checking the mailbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.05,0:03:40.82,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That person was most likely the culprit who destroyed the toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:46.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}As I thought, something interesting is happening inside this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.95,0:03:54.04,Title,,0,0,0,,The Secret of the Moon, Sun, and Stars\N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Secret of the Moon, Sun, and Stars (Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:58.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know the code was in hiragana?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.73,0:04:00.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.59,0:04:02.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really easy to see when you know where to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.10,0:04:03.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.24,0:04:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, the black sun, the white sun, moon and stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.66,0:04:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As well as the black moon and stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.37,0:04:12.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forms change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.38,0:04:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the one black sun does not change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.68,0:04:20.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In hiragana, what's the only character that stands by itself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.12,0:04:23.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one that stands by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.54,0:04:25.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.03,0:04:25.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.93,0:04:28.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's gotta be "n", right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.63,0:04:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.25,0:04:32.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the black sun stands for "n".
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.40,0:04:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second clue is all the engraved lines have one thing in common... The last 3 signs are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They certainly have a special meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.81,0:04:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.32,0:04:55.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we have another clue, The little black and white dots on the right side of some symbols.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:04:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I don't yet know the meaning of the black dot on the bottom right side,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.94,0:05:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the probability that the black and white dots on the upper right side
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.83,0:05:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,stand for the hiragana's daku-ten and the handaku-ten is very high.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.87,0:05:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, daku-ten and handaku-ten, what are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.27,0:05:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't we learn this at school?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.74,0:05:13.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Daku-ten are the symbols that turn the sounds "k","t","s" into "g","d" and "z".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.29,0:05:15.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're called ten-ten as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.98,0:05:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Handaku-ten are the signs that turn "h" in "p", like "pa", "pi", "pu", "pe" and "po".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.68,0:05:22.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if we use the hiragana tables, we can find the matching signs for the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.29,0:05:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, the white moon without a dot, one with a white dot, and one with a black dot,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.34,0:05:31.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can easily understand that the first stands for "h"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.06,0:05:35.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the second for the "b" sounds, and the last for the "p" sounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.30,0:05:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can determine what it stands for, if we use the dakuten and the handakuten!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.50,0:05:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, if we use that as a base, the code written on that glass is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.95,0:05:54.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we look at the first part, third sound is "n" and the forth begins with "p"...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.88,0:05:59.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What words do we have like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:01.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pantei (panties),
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.62,0:06:03.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,heapin (hairpin), perikan (pelican),
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.55,0:06:04.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hanpan (Ham Bread),
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.49,0:06:06.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,meronpan (Melon bread), karepan (Curry bread),
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.96,0:06:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,pasokon (Computer), Nippon (Japan), ran...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,toranpu (playing card)...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.29,0:06:13.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Card! It stands for card!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.69,0:06:17.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! That's gotta be what's written!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:19.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait... then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.94,0:06:22.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see, the code on candle stand would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.25,0:06:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Pu" for the first sound, "ra" for the 4th, and the third sound begins,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.22,0:06:29.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,with a "p"... pu... pu... ra.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.43,0:06:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Puropera (propeller)!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.75,0:06:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! The propeller!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.82,0:06:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But wait, if that black moon stands for "ro", then that means.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.46,0:06:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,propeller... ro... ro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.16,0:06:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miro (look at)?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.73,0:06:44.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Puropera wo miro (look at the propeller)?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.57,0:06:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something written on the plane's propeller!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.96,0:06:50.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.34,0:06:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a dot for the dakuten on the code, so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.04,0:06:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The second sound is "bu", and the thirds is "ra".
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.11,0:06:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,bu ra wo miro...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,bu ra...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.32,0:07:01.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a-bu-ra-e...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.77,0:07:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the oil painting!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.35,0:07:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the portrait, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.39,0:07:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, it's all clear now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.29,0:07:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The code is asking us to look at different things inside the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.87,0:07:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that the code was made up for a special purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.73,0:07:18.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it must've been created to hide something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.07,0:07:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that thing, must be very important!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.76,0:07:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A... A treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.99,0:07:30.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, then to get it we just have to crack the code!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.29,0:07:31.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.05,0:07:32.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.76,0:07:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you really think that there's really a treasure hidden here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.00,0:07:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.60,0:07:40.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure that something is hidden here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.99,0:07:43.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So on the plate it's written.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.69,0:07:49.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The 3rd sound is n, the second is begins with either "b", "z", "g" or "d".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.98,0:07:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,eto... ka-bi-n
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.77,0:07:54.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kabin (vase)!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.40,0:07:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The vase!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.59,0:07:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That one on the dictionary ends with "nro".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.26,0:08:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,eto... n-ro
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.38,0:08:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...da... danro...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.26,0:08:05.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Fireplace!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.49,0:08:08.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then on the mechanical doll, we have...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.86,0:08:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wa-i-n-gu-ra-su.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.95,0:08:13.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the wine glass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.29,0:08:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh... Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.09,0:08:21.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Up until now we've figured out 17 symbols,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.33,0:08:25.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and I can deduce the rest, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.10,0:08:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.30,0:08:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey everyone, look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.31,0:08:33.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the full translation of the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.68,0:08:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Woah, cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look, it's easy to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.67,0:08:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That the suns, stars, and moons, stand for A I U E O.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.32,0:08:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then all we have to do is follow the hiragana order to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.66,0:08:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For example, if you remove one part of the suns and the stars,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.33,0:08:58.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the same with the moons, and you keep removing one after the other, turning clockwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.40,0:09:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They will match the hiragana table.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.49,0:09:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then all we have to do is to complete the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.64,0:09:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.54,0:09:09.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if I translate the whole code we have something like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.01,0:09:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.28,0:09:16.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:18.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the candle stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.38,0:09:19.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the propeller.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.78,0:09:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the oil painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.26,0:09:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the record.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.68,0:09:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the mechanical doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.15,0:09:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the wine glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.08,0:09:28.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.72,0:09:30.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.80,0:09:32.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fireplace!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.16,0:09:34.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the treasure's gotta be there!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.47,0:09:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything like a treasure...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.65,0:09:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.44,0:09:45.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another message.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.76,0:09:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.72,0:09:50.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, bring me what I wrote earlier!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.14,0:09:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.22,0:09:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.59,0:09:56.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So... the code is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.36,0:10:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's written there?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.12,0:10:05.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, please tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.16,0:10:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.20,0:10:07.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.17,0:10:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.27,0:10:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.37,0:10:12.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look at the plate.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.21,0:10:14.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ehh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.30,0:10:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, by plate they mean the plate we already.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.93,0:10:21.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a pile of rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the code was fake after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.68,0:10:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.35,0:10:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like it was a lousy joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.52,0:10:30.31,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A joke? No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.31,0:10:34.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}People don't build such a good secret code for a joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.46,0:10:36.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.90,0:10:39.23,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Did I mistranslate it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.17,0:10:42.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, It cant be that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.37,0:10:45.84,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.36,0:10:51.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What did I miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.58,0:10:55.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What's the true purpose of the code?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.40,0:11:06.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before the police come, let's clean that place and replace the objects where we found them, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.96,0:11:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:17.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.49,0:11:19.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The plate... was up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.03,0:11:20.21,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.21,0:11:23.59,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I change that and begin with the vase.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.59,0:11:26.58,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"sa", "ka, "ro", "ku", "are", "ni", "wa", "to", "fu", "ga".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.98,0:11:28.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No, that leads nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.92,0:11:33.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The vase was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.82,0:11:37.50,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait. What if I write it in romaji?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.50,0:11:39.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The candle stand was on the fireplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.97,0:11:41.45,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nope, that doesn't work either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.70,0:11:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Professor, where was that plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.80,0:11:52.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was near the vase I just put over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.78,0:11:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Near the vase, near the vase...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.74,0:11:59.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hmm, if I try to write it in English?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.01,0:12:02.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait, could it be French... or German maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.95,0:12:05.95,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Darn, it leads nowhere no matter how I change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.06,0:12:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doll, doll.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.06,0:12:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.53,0:12:13.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.87,0:12:21.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.87,0:12:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do something too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.26,0:12:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're staying still in the center of that room, doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.44,0:12:29.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.83,0:12:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you say that the card was in this room too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.15,0:12:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.83,0:12:36.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was there, just under the clock,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:38.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I took it from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.22,0:12:45.13,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So that means that all the things with the code were in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.10,0:12:47.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.30,0:12:50.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If I follow the order of those items.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:52.80,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We start with the plate,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.37,0:12:54.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the vase,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.60,0:12:55.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the candle stand,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:12:57.24,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the propeller,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:58.98,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the oil painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.98,0:13:00.01,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the record,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.34,0:13:01.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the doll,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.81,0:13:03.48,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the wine glass,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.48,0:13:04.51,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the card,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.98,0:13:06.75,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the French dictionary,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:07.76,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}the fireplace,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.76,0:13:09.42,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and the plate again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.22,0:13:12.22,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}They all converge to the center of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.46,0:13:16.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's why Ayumi chan keeps passing near me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.26,0:13:21.65,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But that's strange, there's nothing on the floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.65,0:13:23.60,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}and it looks like nothing has been on the floor for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.23,0:13:25.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then if it's not on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.84,0:13:33.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There! At the base of the chandelier!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.18,0:13:37.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor, pull me up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.33,0:13:37.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.03,0:13:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.28,0:13:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.19,0:13:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.96,0:13:54.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh... What's that noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.46,0:13:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wha... what's happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.07,0:14:02.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the second floor, It sounds like something fell down.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.44,0:14:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.79,0:14:25.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}So, the room just above the one we were in...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.10,0:14:30.30,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.24,0:14:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.04,0:14:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's a stair case in the room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.08,0:14:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, that's what the point was!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.78,0:14:46.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The code was pointing at the chandelier in the middle of the ceiling...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.95,0:14:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, at this secret staircase.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.64,0:14:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My uncle loved mechanisms like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.06,0:14:57.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But really, to do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.56,0:15:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe there's still a treasure there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:05.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, something is hidden up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.47,0:15:07.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.57,0:15:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Err, What's with this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.52,0:15:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's all dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.71,0:15:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't see a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.95,0:15:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second... Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:27.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are tiny parts of a 1 yen coin and... a tube of oil paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.36,0:15:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, there's something on the desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.69,0:15:33.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.93,0:15:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.80,0:15:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-s-s-s...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.51,0:15:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Talk clearly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.97,0:15:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A skeleton!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.71,0:15:49.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.68,0:15:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.35,0:15:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one I mentioned earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who used to hide here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.29,0:16:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who whittled the one yen coin and made up the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.80,0:16:10.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be... was he killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.30,0:16:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it looks like he was alive when he was writing a letter to your aunt.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.91,0:16:20.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems he had a weak heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.05,0:16:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why was he living here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only ones who ever lived here were my aunt and uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.82,0:16:30.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there was someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.55,0:16:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before your uncle died, someone came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.66,0:16:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before my uncle died?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.86,0:16:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.51,0:16:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the portrait of your aunt and uncle near the fireplace...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.60,0:16:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who painted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.80,0:16:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure he became aware of this secret place, when he stayed here to paint...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.58,0:16:54.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, but why did he stay hidden here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:58.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did he keep sending postcards to my aunt?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.21,0:17:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason must be this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.85,0:17:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.95,0:17:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.39,0:17:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.99,0:17:09.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,20 dollar bill plate?! Counterfeit money?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.26,0:17:14.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'm sure he was asked by someone to counterfeit money.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.66,0:17:21.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he changed his mind and had to disappear and hide from that someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.50,0:17:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he hid here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.48,0:17:27.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He stayed here because he was ashamed of what he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.81,0:17:33.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he wrote to your aunt in code, because he wanted her to know of this secret place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.95,0:17:38.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, the person who checked my aunt's mailbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.22,0:17:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's probably the one who asked the man to make the counterfeits...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.46,0:17:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the one who destroyed the toys, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.46,0:17:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.03,0:17:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, I kept an eye on that old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.49,0:17:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I knew he was going to find the thing I was looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.42,0:17:59.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when I looked inside the box, there were only toys.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.88,0:18:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.81,0:18:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I searched this mansion for a long time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.95,0:18:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I searched it all, but I never thought of a secret hidden room...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.00,0:18:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.86,0:18:20.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.88,0:18:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unless you want to see someone die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.40,0:18:30.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, if you'd used your head, you wouldn't have gotten involved in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.76,0:18:31.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.11,0:18:39.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The young lady over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.12,0:18:42.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.29,0:18:47.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grab the plate from the old geezer, and give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:50.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.16,0:18:55.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There, you're a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.46,0:19:00.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come a little closer and I'll give you a nice reward...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.51,0:19:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.87,0:19:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna beat you to a pulp!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.55,0:19:10.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.31,0:19:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll give it to you right away...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.98,0:19:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister Okuda Tomoaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.83,0:19:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.71,0:19:20.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How do you know my name?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.96,0:19:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I asked that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.19,0:19:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He can't talk anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.56,0:19:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure? If you listen closely, you might hear the voice of his ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.04,0:19:37.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha ha ha... Brat, there's no such thing as...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.91,0:19:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okuda Tomoaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.25,0:19:46.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okuda Tomoaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.88,0:19:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okuda Tomoaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.15,0:19:55.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okuda Tomoaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.23,0:20:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me keep my promise, and give this back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.80,0:20:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Catch this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.95,0:20:18.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.68,0:20:19.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.29,0:20:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, or the ghost might come back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.40,0:20:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're talking about that voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.12,0:20:26.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was only this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.96,0:20:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Masked Yaiba voice changer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.56,0:20:33.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recorded my voice when I said his name, slowed and then amplified it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.20,0:20:38.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know his name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.94,0:20:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that was written in code in the letter on his desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.89,0:20:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It said "The one who coerced me into this was Okuda Tomoaki".
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, so that's why he was writing her letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted to thank her for letting him stay here...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.52,0:21:03.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to your aunt?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:07.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She died last year. She was 76.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.96,0:21:10.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like I'm the last one now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.80,0:21:19.17,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We'll never know, but maybe there was more than a simple "thank you" in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.39,0:22:50.85,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Two hours later, the police came and Okuda Tomoaki was arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.85,0:22:53.64,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And we were finally able to go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.44,0:22:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I still don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.47,0:22:59.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.61,0:23:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, those words your father said.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.68,0:23:06.11,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}"For sure, Professor Agasa, you're a real sunshine!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.32,0:23:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since that time, he keeps calling me "Professor Sunshine".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.62,0:23:15.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.06,0:23:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a play on words...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.02,0:23:18.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A play on words?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.49,0:23:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you write your name with the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.62,0:23:22.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.23,0:23:26.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,A - GA - SA
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.10,0:23:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, you only use suns to write it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.10,0:23:30.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.22,0:23:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's kinda neat,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.85,0:23:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am Professor Sunshine!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.72,0:23:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? There's someone there!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.20,0:23:56.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.24,0:23:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was someone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.60,0:23:58.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means... that we are not alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.60,0:24:00.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just... to keep us silent...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.21,0:24:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't accept it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.64,0:24:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.39,0:24:09.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Run, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.05,0:24:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.55,0:24:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Case of Disappearing Detective Boys
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.72,0:24:17.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's HINT!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.99,0:24:19.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A bunch of puppets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.62,0:24:22.46,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Next time, your gonna see the Detective Club's great skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.46,0:24:23.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm really excited!
